SUMMARY:Marjorie Prime at 6th Street Playhouse
DESCRIPTION:In Marjorie Prime\, playwright Jordan Harrison delves into the intricate dance between human memory and artificial intelligence. Set in the not-so-distant future\, the narrative centers on 85-year-old Marjorie\, whose mind is gradually succumbing to dementia. To combat her fading recollections\, her family introduces her to a “Prime”—a lifelike holographic projection of her late husband\, Walter\, programmed to retell the stories of their shared past. As Marjorie interacts with Walter Prime\, the lines between authentic memories and reconstructed narratives blur…
URL:https://golocal.coop/event/marjorie-prime-at-6th-street-playhouse-9/
LOCATION:6th Street Playhouse Monroe Stage\, 52 W 6th Street\, Santa Rosa\, CA\, 95401\, United States
CATEGORIES:Theater
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://golocal.coop/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Marjorie-prime-6th-street-playhouse-s.jpg
END:VEVENT
